social_posts.post_text: In the span of like 5 years I won 3 championships overseas, last year probably would’ve been my 4th and not sure where things would’ve finished in Champions league, it’s interesting going through pictures or clips of things because all the memories surrounding those moments come back, not just the specific moment captured in the picture or video. It’s a lot of ups and downs that go into the behind the scenes life of a professional athlete, most only see the good, but there’s struggles and rough times as well, in every one of those years I had to deal with adversity on a personal level as well as adversity as a team, even the championship teams I was on had obstacles we had to overcome but we always accepted the task, and made it happen, no matter what it took. Things get a little turbulent sometimes but it’s never obstacle or the things you’re dealing with, it’s what you chose to do in response to them that really matters, I’m grateful for the life I’ve lived and what me and my teammates over the years have accomplished, I’ve had the luxury of meeting and playing with alot of great players over the course of my career, still friends with a lot of them still today. Still alot left in the tank and still many more things to accomplish. The goals are always the same… take it as high as you can while you can

#7DAYSMagicMoment

I celebrated another year around the globe recently. I learned a lot in the last year… about myself, and just about life. Faced some adversity, overcame struggles and problems. Made some great additions to my life.. ideas, thoughts, people, Min alskade, pretty much trying to constantly evolve and become a better version of myself and try to create the best life possible… I’m grateful for all the ups and downs, the good and the bad, because without trials and tribulations there’s no growth, and without great times and happiness there’s nothing to look forward to. Thank you to everybody that reached out and told me happy birthday and thank you to everybody that’s been in my corner and has loved and supported and been there for me in anyway… I appreciate you all. Happy 32rd birthday to me 😉😏🎁
